CV was performed with prepared biphasic La2O3/La2O2C2 polymorphs for the estimation of the material behavior towards the electrochemical behavior. The oxidative current (I

                           pa
                        ) for the bare electrode taken as a reference, was found 0.8297 mA (100 %) and for the La2O3/La2O2C2 electrode, the current was increased and obtained 0.8799 mA which was 6.05 % more than the bare ITO electrode whereas under the enzymatic condition, the electrode behavior was found more appropriate with the oxidative current value 1.011 mA which was 16.52 % increased from bare ITO electrode. Fig. 8(B). The electrochemical behavior of the La2O3/La2O2C2/ITO electrode was found in good response as the biphasic polymorphs play appreciable role. The quantum-sized carbon nanoparticles provide an auspicious route to enhance the electrical conductivity whereas lanthanum oxide and carbide nanoparticles, having variable valancy and oxidation state of lanthanum, provide rich electronic availability. Moreover, after the drop-casting tyrosinase enzyme, the electrode, functions as a bioelectrode where the copper metal of the enzymes functions as a catalyst increases the oxidation and reduction process during the course of the reaction. This is supported by the Yasuyuki Matoba et al., 2018, who reported a work on the catalytic activity of tyrosinase enzyme where the active center of dinuclear copper present in the tyrosinase enzyme catalyzed the conversion of phenol to ortho-quinone [46].

The reusability of the prepared bioelectrode was obtained in a similar phosphate buffer solution. In this experiment 20 times scan was demonstrated where the anodic peak current value (I

                           pa
                        ) was found optimum value at 13th scan, considered as 100 %, further at 14th and 15th scan the current value was found 1.92 % and 1.56 % decreased and remains constant up to 20 scan which was found to be 1.21 % decreased from 18th to 20th scan that's why the reusability of the prepared electrode was found 20 days Fig. 10(B).
